  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hmm, this indeed seems to be a bug where the ui state in routing only seems to reflect the direct state of an index that gets repeated (in this case with the root one). A workaround is making sure there's a different query for the root as for that unique index. \r\n\r\nIn my example I made sure the root index gets `__root__` as index name / index id, which then gets filtered out in the implementation for the search client.\r\n\r\nhttps://codesandbox.io/s/competent-sky-cex6n?file=/src/App.vue\r\n\r\nI think this *is* a bug somehow in the routing, but not sure what the solution it up to now. Workaround is making sure no index names / index id's are repeated",
    "created_at": "2021-10-25T15:00:19Z",
